com.apriori.collections

Class TransformingMap.Bidi<KI,VI,KO,VO>

  • java.lang.Object

  • Type Parameters:
    KI - the "input" key type; the type of keys in the wrapped map
    VI - the "input" value type; the type of values in the wrapped map
    KO - the "output" key type; the type of keys in this map
    VO - the "output" value type; the type of values in this map
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<KO,VO>
    Enclosing class:
    TransformingMap<KI,VI,KO,VO>

    public static class TransformingMap.Bidi<KI,VI,KO,VO>
extends TransformingMap<KI,VI,KO,VO>
    A transforming map that can transform keys and values in both directions. Since this map can transform in the other direction (output type -> input type), all operations are supported, including put(Object, Object) and putAll(Map).

    Several methods are overridden to use the reverse function before delegating to the underlying map. Since some of these interface methods actually accept any type of object (instead of requiring the map's key type), this implementation could result in ClassCastExceptions if objects with incorrect types are passed to them. These methods are containsKey(Object), get(Object), and remove(Object).
